5 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2404, is
6 amended to read as follows:
7 Section 2404. A. Scholarships awarded under the Oklahoma State
8 Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program shall be awarded to
9 all eligible applicants without any limitation on the number of
10 scholarships to be awarded in any year other than the amount of
11 funds available for the scholarship program and the number of
12 eligible applicants.
13 B. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education may, at the
14 time a scholarship is awarded to a student, set aside in the
15 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Trust Fund
16 funds for the full five-year commitment made to such eligible
17 scholar. For all academic years, students who have previously
18 received academic scholarships under the provisions of this act and
19 who have continued at all times to fulfill the requirements for
20 eligibility to receive academic scholarships provided in this act
21 shall be given an absolute priority for continued financial support
22 by the Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award
23 Program superior to any students who are applying for such academic
24 scholarships awards for the first time.
Req. No. 13243 Page 8
1 C. In addition to the qualifications specified in Section 2403
2 of this title, the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education may
3 adopt additional criteria for selection and allocation of awards
4 which may include, but are not limited to, consideration of high
5 school academic performance and personal interviews. The Oklahoma
6 State Regents for Higher Education shall annually report on the
7 number of former Academic Rising Scholars Award Program participants
8 who stay in state as compared to those who leave Oklahoma within
9 five (5) years of leaving the Award Program. In addition, the
10 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education are hereby authorized to
11 determine a maximum number of awards or a maximum amount of funding
12 which may go to nonresident students. Such maximum limitations
13 shall not exceed twenty-five percent (25%) of the awards or amount
14 of funding in any category provided in paragraph 2 of subsection A
15 of Section 2403 of this title.
16 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2405, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 2405. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education
19 may adopt rules and regulations, prescribe and provide appropriate
20 forms for application, and employ such persons, contract for such
21 services and make such additional expenditures as may be necessary
22 or appropriate for implementing the provisions of the Oklahoma State
23 Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Act; provided, as part of
24 the regulations adopted for administration of the provisions of the
Req. No. 13243 Page 9
1 Okla homa State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program, the
2 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education shall require that each
3 scholarship recipient make continuing and satisfactory progress
4 toward a degree, including the establishment of an annual minimum
5 grade point average and annual minimum credit hours to be maintained
6 by the participants. Such regulations shall also provide for
7 revoking or rescinding assistance to any scholarship recipient who
8 fails to meet such required standards. Such regulations shall also
9 provide that the funds made available to students as part of the
10 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program shall
11 be paid directly to the institution of the student's choice, in
12 trust for the student, and on the student's behalf, and shall
13 contain appropriate restrictions and conditions that such monies are
14 expended only for the purposes authorized by this act. Such
15 regulations shall also provide for portability of award for a
16 recipient among accredited institutions of higher education in
17 Oklahoma in which the recipient may enroll as long as the recipient
18 meets requirements of the program; however, waivers shall only be
19 portable between institutions in The Oklahoma State System of Higher
20 Education and waiver portability may be further limited by the
21 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education rules and regulations.
22 SECTION 6. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2406, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
Req. No. 13243 Page 10
1 Section 2406. The Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising
2 Scholars Award Act shall not be construed as granting any authority
3 to control or influence the policies of any educational institution
4 because it accepts students who are participating in the scholarship
5 program, or to require any such institution to admit, or once
6 admitted to continue in such institution, any participant in the
7 scholarship program.
8 SECTION 7. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 2407, is
9 amended to read as follows:
10 Section 2407. As part of its duties in administering the
11 Oklahoma State Regents' Academic Rising Scholars Award Program, the
12 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, in cooperation with the
13 State Board of Education, shall encourage Oklahoma high school
14 juniors who plan to attend college to take the Preliminary
15 Scholastic Aptitude Test/National Merit Scholarship Qualifying Test
16 in their junior year in high school as preparation for taking the
17 Scholastic Aptitude Test their senior year in high school.
18 SECTION 8. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
19 SECTION 9. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
